Interface IRestExternalState

    Class to represent an ExternalState object.

    • Method Detail

      • getState

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> getState()
        Get the properties of this ExternalState object. The value objects in the map may be of any type supported by the Interop component: String, Integer, Long, Boolean, or Timestamp.

        Note: BigDecimal support is pending.

        Returns:
        the map of replicated external properties; may be empty; never null

      • setState

        void setState(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,?> state)
        Set the properties of this ExternalState object. The value objects in the map may be of any type supported by the Interop component: String, Integer, Long, Boolean, or Timestamp.

        These properties are added to the current set of properties already set for this object.

        Note: BigDecimal support is pending.

        Parameters:
        state - the map of replicated external properties to store; may be empty; never null

      • removeState

        void removeState(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> names)
        Remove properties from this ExternalState object.
        Parameters:
        names - the set of property names to remove.
